metadata.name: Undying need for nostalgia  #8
metadata.description:
Symbols represent culture, and cultures are the result of collective wisdom over a long period of time. Because of this, people tend to preserve symbols, and some are willing to pay millions of dollars to trade cultural artifacts. The collection in front of you is a sign of the cultural memories of world music (the top 100 singers of all time, selected and published by Rolling Stone Magazine).

We have used the top 10 singers on this list to make this collection:

Aretha Franklin
Ray Charles
Elvis Presley
Sam Cooke
John Lennon
Marvin Gaye
Bob Dylan
Otis Redding
Stevie Wonder
James Brown

Each NFT of this set is unique (two different sides of cassettes A and B).

Note: This collection goes beyond '' Our goal is to create a unique feature mark for the music.

Their name is eternal.

metadata.name: Truchet Towers #155
metadata.description:
Curved Truchet tiling is laid down on a 3D plane forming an imaginary landscape of ripples.

The longest continuous line created by the tiling is removed, cutting a path through the terrain.
This occurs within 3D space and may or may not appear within the confines of the canvas frame,
but most likely will appear.

A tower rises up to wherever a circle is created by the tiling. Driven by the random
tiling, zero or several of these may appear within the frame. Shadows differ in each mint.

In addition to working on decorative tiling, Sébastien Truchet worked on canals and sundials,
forming the inspiration for the exploration of shade and shadow in this work.

Mints will have a variety of earth-tone background colors with each perspective of the scene
slightly different to produce diverse results.

As I researched Sébastien Truchet I learned that he worked with hydraulics and canal design,
as well as sundials. This became the inspiration for my new shading and shadowing technique used
in this piece.

For me this piece evokes a sense of agriculture, and connects me to an imaginary
landscape that could have looked familiar to Truchet in 18th century France.

This work was created with my own javascript, utilizing my polyline path helper library I
maintain at https://github.com/markroland/path-helper.

metadata.name: Yellow House #184
metadata.description:
It is very easy to forget the beauty of the places we consume because they are available to us by nature.
The things we consume all our lives we find not so special.
It’s very hard to remember how special and valuable these things really are.

With this work, I will try to give sincere admiration and respect to my favorite place on the beach!

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 'f' to save .png with resolution = 4000px x 4000px

Created using p5js ,100% p5.js code and math.

@Mutart, April, 2022.

metadata.name: Moonlight Impression #99
metadata.description:
I always love to feel the moonlight falling on the mountains and flowing clouds. There is always a scenery in deep inside, it is the kind of picture that you might think of when you are  alone in the deep night. In my case, that's somewhere there's a yellow moon.

This piece presents the combination of the yellow moon with different elements such as mountains, forests and clouds in some transformations.

Many dots of different sizes and colors are used to paint the picture, trying to replicate the texture of a glue painting.

Made with p5js.


Variables:
- 27 sky color schemas
- 27 mountain color schemas

Control(in live view):
- Press [s] to save a high-res png image

metadata.name: Organicon, variation 00 - special edition #323
metadata.description:
Thank you!

Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
One of 640 special edition generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation 00 is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. A small counter in the lower-right corner displays the progress.

Interface: on first load the piece operates in active mode. In this mode an iteration is cleared 30s after completion and replaced by the next iteration. This mode is indicated by a flashing dot in the upper-right corner.

A first mouse click disables active mode. The current iteration will complete and remain on screen. A second mouse click clears the screen, loads the next iteration, and reenables active mode.

metadata.name: Grove #119
metadata.description:
A generative, impressionist painting of a small grove of trees in one of the four seasons. In spring and summer, flowers bloom in the meadow. A rare variation will create a charcoal drawing on white or black paper. Super rare will create a lighted winter scene that may have a moon behind the tree.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press 's' to save a screenshot at any point. Image size is 1400x1082px.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 3,000 px.

On the paintings only, adding '&bg=true' will stop the painting after the background. Adding '&size=3000&bg=true' will give you a nice desktop background! 

Common Features:
- About 12-14 trees
- One of the four seasons
- One of 12 highlight color tints
- One of 12 shadow color tints
- Varying levels of distance haze
- Varying max brush sizes
- Varying amount of colors in the strokes

Less Common
- 15% chance of a charcoal drawing
- 50% chance it to be a dark winter scene

Rare
- Winter drawing with lights on the tree

Super Rare
- Winter drawing with a moon behind the tree

metadata.name: Yaff #271
metadata.description:
I used this collection to teach my daughter a little bit about generative art. We enjoyed working on it so much that I wanted to share it so she could see it out in the wild.

All primary sales proceeds will be donated to bellyful, a local charity supporting new parents.

Keyboard shortcuts:
"s" - Save hi-res image
"p" - Start/stop animation
"o" - Show/hide particle tails (when animating)
